sentences: In the 1940s, he played as a pianist in the Hotclub Combo which he cofounded with Emil Mangelsdorff and others.
In 1987, he was a cofounder of the Rheingau Musik Festival.
Jung learned to play the piano with Emma Lübbecke-Job among others, and later the violin and the viola, performing in public for the first time in 1935.
As a student, he co-founded the Hotclub Combo in 1941, playing as the group's pianist with Carlo Bohländer, Emil Mangelsdorff, Hans Podehl and Charly Petry.
In 1943, he also learned to play the double bass, and served as the group's bassist from 1945 to 1948 in the Hotclub Sextet.

Jung was the president of the Wiesbaden association of artists and art lovers (Verein der Künstler und Kunstfreunde) from 1976.
In 1987, he was a co-founder and patron of the Rheingau Musik Festival.
He had an accident in the winter 2008/09 when he attended a concert of his friend Menahem Pressler in Hamburg, and died in Rüdesheim.
The broadcaster Hessischer Rundfunk aired in 1946/47 a show with him as the solo pianist, playing in the style of Teddy Wilson.
